{"title_page": "2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|timestamp=20200402133413|year=2020|month=April|day=2|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|date=2 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox event\n| title                    = <!-- Title to display, if other than page name -->\n| image                    =\n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  =\n| native_name              = \n| native_name_lang         = \n| english_name             = \n| time                     =\n| duration                 = \n| date                     = 1 March - 21 March (congregation) \n| venue                    =  [[Banglewali Mosque|Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]] \n| location                 = [[Nizamuddin West]], [[Delhi]], India\n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            = Nizamuddin Markaz hotspot\n| type                     = Religious congregation \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = \n| motive                   =\n| target                   = \n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organisers               = <!-- or |organizers= -->\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             =atleast 9000 people \n| awards                   = \n| url                      = \n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| notes                    = \n}}\n\nA [[Tablighi Jamaat]] religious congregation that took place in Delhi's [[Banglewali Mosque|Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]] in early March has emerged as a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] [[super-spreader]] event, after more than 400 confirmed cases and at least 10 deaths linked to the event were reported across the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=India confronts its first coronavirus \u2018super-spreader\u2019 \u2014 a Muslim missionary group with more than 400 members infected |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/india-coronavirus-tablighi-jamaat-delhi/2020/04/02/abdc5af0-7386-11ea-ad9b-254ec99993bc_story.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Washington Post}}</ref> The congregation was attended by people from various states in India as well as 960 foreigners from 40 countries.<ref>{{cite news |title=379 Indonesians among foreigners from 40 countries attended Tablighi Jamaat gathering: Sources |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/379-indonesians-among-foreigners-from-40-countries-attended-tablighi-jamaat-gathering-sources20200403152720/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=ANI}}</ref>\n\nTablighi Jamaat has received widespread criticism from the Muslim community for holding the congregation despite a ban on public gatherings being issued by the [[Government of Delhi]] on 13 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat draws widespread condemnation from Muslim society |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/academics-among-muslims-condemn-the-act-of-tablighi-jamaat-in-nizamuddin/article31218658.ece |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Hindu Business Line}}</ref> According to the Home Ministry, there were 1,746 people in the Markaz on 21 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat's defiance spreads concern {{!}} India Today Insight |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/web-exclusive/story/the-new-threat-from-tablighi-jamaat-1661938-2020-04-01 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref>\n\n==Attendees==\n\nAt least 9000 attendees from all over the country and from abroad participated in the congregation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/americans-british-among-960-foreign-tablighi-jamaat-members-blacklisted-visas-cancelled-2563029.html|title=Americans, British Among 960 Foreign Tablighi Jamaat Members Blacklisted, Visas Cancelled|website=News18|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/1400-nizamuddin-event-attendees-from-maha-traced-tope/articleshow/74965665.cms|title=1,400 Nizamuddin event attendees from Maha traced: Tope|date=2020-04-03|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Over 800 Indonesian and Malaysian preachers present. Many of these attendees are untraceable and are absconding.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/india/1828919/delhis-tablighi-jamaat-event-becomes-indias-coronavirus-hotspot/|title=A religious congregation in Delhi could be the coronavirus hotspot India was trying to escape|first=Niharika|last=Sharma|website=Quartz India}}</ref> 281 foreigners among 1830 people who had been staying at the mosque since 8 March were found by Delhi Police.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nAbout 200 people have shown symptoms of COVID-19 of which, 53 people have been confirmed positive in Delhi.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-52104753|title=India event sparks massive search for Covid-19 cases|date=2020-03-31|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-31|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/opinion/tablighi-jamaat-congregation-and-how-religion-has-been-the-super-spreader-of-coronavirus/392531/|title=Tablighi Jamaat congregation and how religion has been the 'super spreader' of coronavirus|last=Team|first=ThePrint|date=2020-04-01|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gulte.com/news/83733/More-Than-330-Cases-Linked-to-Delhi-Mosque|title=More Than 330 Cases Linked to Delhi Mosque|last=13|date=2020-04-02|website=Gulte|language=english|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> The state of [[Tamil Nadu]] reported more than 190 cases linked to the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-india-delhi-markaz-nizamuddin-mosque-sealed-after-7-covid-19-deaths-850-moved-out-for-qu-2203336|title=50 Coronavirus Cases In Tamil Nadu After Delhi Mosque Event: 10 Points|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nThere was Ijtema (congregation) in every week of March till March 21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/2100-foreigners-visited-india-for-tablighi-activities-this-year-mha/articleshow/74915572.cms|title=2100 foreigners visited India for Tablighi activities this year: MHA|date=March 31, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/nizamuddin-corona-cases-govts-race-to-curb-spread-as-hundreds-from-tablighi-meet-show-coronavirus-symptoms/articleshow/74921860.cms|title=Nizamuddin corona cases: Govts race to curb spread as hundreds from Tablighi meet show symptoms &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> There were also other violation of rules by foreign speakers including misuse of tourist visa for missionary activities and not taking 14-day home quarantine for travellers from abroad.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Singh|first=Vijaita|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/home-ministry-to-blacklist-800-tablighi-preachers-from-indonesia-for-violation-of-visa-rules/article31214048.ece|title=Home Ministry asked States to identify 824 foreign Tablighi members|date=2020-03-31|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> It is believed that the sources of infection were preachers from Indonesia. At least 24 of the attendees had tested positive for the virus among 300 who showed symptom by 31 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-52104753 |title=Coronavirus: Search for hundreds of people after Delhi prayer meeting |date=31 March 2020 |work=BBC }}</ref> Many had returned to their states and also provided refuge to foreign speakers without the knowledge of local governments.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Saravanan|first=S. p|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/covid-19-five-tourists-from-thailand-admitted-to-isolation-ward-at-erode-hospital/article31088949.ece|title=COVID-19 {{!}} Five tourists from Thailand admitted to isolation ward at Erode hospital|date=2020-03-17|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> and eventually started local transmissions especially in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[Telengana]], [[Karnataka]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]] and [[Assam]]. On 16 March 2020, Delhi Government ordered that no religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 will be allowed in Delhi till 31 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/covid-19-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-protests-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-mar-31/articleshow/74650645.cms|title=Coronavirus in Delhi: No religious, social, political gatherings, protests of over 50 in Delhi till Mar 31 &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-outbreak-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-march-31/articleshow/74650421.cms?from=mdr|title=Coronavirus outbreak: No religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 in Delhi till March 31|date=March 16, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> As of 30 March 2020 the entire [[Nizamuddin West]] area has been cordoned off by the Police and medical camps have been set up.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/coronavirus-200-people-from-nizamuddin-develop-symptoms-area-cordoned-off/article31204617.ece|title=Coronavirus &#124; 200 people in Nizamuddin develop symptoms; area cordoned off|first=Saurabh|last=Trivedi|date=March 30, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref> After evacuation from the markaz, of the scores of jamaat attendees, 167 of them were quarantined in a railway facility in south east Delhi amid concerns over their safety and transmission of the virus. There were further complications after the staff at the quarantine facility reported the Tablighi jamaat followers misbehaved with the staff and spit at the doctors looking after them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-india-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-misbehave-staffers-spit-doctors-delhi-quarantine-units-1662322-2020-04-01|title=Tablighi Jamaat attendees misbehave with staffers, spit at doctors at Delhi quarantine units|last=DelhiApril 1|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=April 1|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02|last3=Ist|first3=2020 22:59}}</ref>\n\nAdministration of TJ had said they are willing to dispatch hundreds of missionary to their respective nation & states but as the lockdown is in place they are helpless.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/nizamuddin-markaz-had-sought-help-from-authorities-for-vacating-premises/article31214305.ece|title=Nizamuddin markaz had sought help from authorities for vacating premises|first=Staff|last=Reporter|date=March 31, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>Press Release and relevant letters released by the Markaz</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://khabar.ndtv.com/news/india/coronavirus-total-case-in-india-nizamuddin-markaz-organiser-says-continuously-asking-curfew-pass-and-2203440|title=\u0915\u094c\u0928 \u0939\u0948 '\u0918\u094b\u0930 \u0905\u092a\u0930\u093e\u0927\u0940': \u0905\u0917\u0930 \u0924\u092c\u0932\u0940\u0917\u0940 \u091c\u092e\u093e\u0924 \u0928\u0947 \u092e\u093e\u0902\u0917\u093e \u0925\u093e 17 \u0917\u093e\u0921\u093c\u093f\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092b\u094d\u092f\u0942 \u092a\u093e\u0938, \u0924\u094b \u0915\u093f\u0938\u0928\u0947 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u0938\u0941\u0928\u0940 \u092c\u093e\u0924|website=NDTVIndia}}</ref>\n\n==Cases linked==\n\nAccording health authorities, until 2. April, among 2000 positive cases in India nearly 400 cases epidemiological linkage can be traced to the Tablighi Jamaat cluster.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/one-in-indias-five-covid-19-patients-is-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-and-its-delhi-event/393993/|title=One in India\u2019s five Covid-19 patients is linked to Tablighi Jamaat and its Delhi event|last=Yadavar|first=Swagata|date=2020-04-02|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/400-covid-19-cases-with-linkage-to-tablighi-jamaat-found-health-ministry/articleshow/74951562.cms|title=400 COVID-19 cases with linkage to Tablighi Jamaat found: Health Ministry {{!}} India News - Times of India|last=Apr 2|first=ANI {{!}}|last2=2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03|last3=Ist|first3=18:55}}</ref> By 3.April, 647 cases are reported related to this cluster.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/647-positive-cases-from-14-states-in-last-two-days-are-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-health-ministry/articleshow/74967407.cms|title=647 coronavirus positive cases from 14 states in last two days are linked to Tablighi Jamaat: Health Ministry|date=2020-04-03|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Following are some of the  positive cases from different states as reported in media.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! State or UT !! Positive Cases\n!Deaths!! Ref(s)\n|-\n|[[Andaman and Nicobar Islands|Andman and Nicobar]]|| 9\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|[[Andhra Pradesh|Andhra pradesh]]|| 140 \n|1||<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://english.jagran.com/india/coronavirus-outbreak-295-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-test-positive-for-covid19-960-foreign-attendees-blacklisted-by-mha-10010317|title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Nizamuddin Markaz trail widens with sharp spike in cases in Telangana, Delhi and UP|date=2020-04-03|website=Jagran English|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Assam]]|| 16\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n| [[Arunachal Pradesh]]  || 1 \n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-arunachal-pradesh-registers-first-covid-19-case-after-31-year-old-tablighi-jamaat-attendee-tests-positive-8219381.html|title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Arunachal Pradesh registers first COVID-19 case after 31-year-old Tablighi Jamaat attendee tests positive|website=Firstpost|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Bihar]]\n|{{ndash}}\n|1\n|\n|-\n| [[Delhi]]|| 152\n|2||<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/arvind-kejriwal-delhi-cm-pc-total-cases-tablighi-jamaat-link-coronavirus-covid19-1662684-2020-04-02|title=Delhi coronavirus toll rises to 4, total cases now 293, half of these linked to Tablighi meet: CM Kejriwal|last=DelhiApril 2|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=April 2|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03|last3=Ist|first3=2020 23:10}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Gujarat]]\n|{{ndash}}\n|1\n|\n|-\n|[[Himachal Pradesh]]|| 3\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n| [[Jammu and Kashmir]]|| 22\n|2||<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n| [[Karnataka]]|| 11\n|1||<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|[[Maharashtra]]\n|{{ndash}}\n|2\n|\n|-\n|[[Puducherry]]|| 2\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":1\" />\n|-\n|[[Rajasthan]]|| 16\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/jaipur/seven-more-covid-19-cases-in-rajasthan-count-rises-to-140/articleshow/74959836.cms|title=Seven more Covid-19 cases in Rajasthan, count rises to 140 {{!}} Jaipur News - Times of India|last=Apr 3|first=ANI {{!}} Updated:|last2=2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03|last3=Ist|first3=09:15}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Tamil Nadu]]|| 190\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/in-tn-190-from-tablighi-cluster-test-positive/articleshow/74940016.cms|title=In TN, 190 from Tablighi cluster test positive {{!}} India News - Times of India|last=Narayan|first=Pushpa|last2=Apr 2|first2=Jaya Menon {{!}} TNN {{!}}|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03|last3=2020|last4=Ist|first4=03:06}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Telangana]]|| 50\n|9||<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.daijiworld.com/news/newsDisplay.aspx?newsID=691949|title=Tablighi super spreaders cause Covid-19 explosion in India|website=www.daijiworld.com|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Uttar Pradesh]]|| 42\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|}\n\n*\n\n\n==Action==\n\nDelhi government ordered an FIR against [[Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi]], the head of Nizamuddin faction of the Tablighi Jamat.<ref name=\"standard\">{{cite web |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-120033100007_1.html |website=business-standard |publisher=[[Business Standard]] |accessdate=30 March 2020 |date=30 March 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatoday\">{{cite web |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-1661514-2020-03-30 |website=India Today |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref> On 31 March 2020, FIR was filed against [[Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi]] and others by Delhi Police Crime Branch under Section 3 (penalty for offence) of the [[Epidemic Diseases Act, 1897]] and Sections 269 (Negligent act likely to spread infection of disease), 270 (malignant act likely to spread infection of disease), 271 (disobedience to quarantine rule) and 120b (punishment of criminal conspiracy) of the IPC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-in-india-tablighi-jamaat-preacher-others-booked-for-violating-govt-guidelines-on-religious-gatherings-1661870-2020-03-31|title=Coronavirus in India: Tablighi Jamaat preacher, others booked for violating govt guidelines on religious gatherings|first1=India Today Web Desk New|last1=DelhiMarch 31|first2=2020UPDATED:|last2=March 31|first3=2020 21:56|last3=Ist|website=India Today}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in India}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in India]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in India]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|timestamp=20200402133413|year=2020|month=April|day=2|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|date=2 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox event\n| title                    = <!-- Title to display, if other than page name -->\n| image                    =\n| image_upright            = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  =\n| native_name              = \n| native_name_lang         = \n| english_name             = \n| time                     =\n| duration                 = \n| date                     = 1 March - 21 March (congregation) \n| venue                    =  [[Banglewali Mosque|Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]] \n| location                 = [[Nizamuddin West]], [[Delhi]], India\n| coordinates              = <!-- {{coord|LAT|LON|region:XXXX_type:event|display=inline,title}} -->\n| also_known_as            = Nizamuddin Markaz hotspot\n| type                     = Religious congregation \n| theme                    = \n| cause                    = \n| motive                   =\n| target                   = \n| first_reporter           = \n| budget                   = \n| patron                   = <!-- or |patrons= -->\n| organisers               = <!-- or |organizers= -->\n| filmed_by                = \n| participants             =atleast 9000 people \n| awards                   = \n| url                      = \n| blank_label              = <!-- or |blank_data= -->\n| blank1_label             = <!-- or |blank1_data= -->\n| blank2_label             = <!-- or |blank2_data= -->\n| website                  = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| notes                    = \n}}\n\nA [[Tablighi Jamaat]] religious congregation that took place in Delhi's [[Banglewali Mosque|Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]] in early March has emerged as a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] [[super-spreader]] event, after more than 400 confirmed cases and at least 10 deaths linked to the event were reported across the country.<ref>{{cite news |title=India confronts its first coronavirus \u2018super-spreader\u2019 \u2014 a Muslim missionary group with more than 400 members infected |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/india-coronavirus-tablighi-jamaat-delhi/2020/04/02/abdc5af0-7386-11ea-ad9b-254ec99993bc_story.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Washington Post}}</ref> The congregation was attended by people from various states in India as well as 960 foreigners from 40 countries.<ref>{{cite news |title=379 Indonesians among foreigners from 40 countries attended Tablighi Jamaat gathering: Sources |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/379-indonesians-among-foreigners-from-40-countries-attended-tablighi-jamaat-gathering-sources20200403152720/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=ANI}}</ref>\n\nTablighi Jamaat has received widespread criticism from the Muslim community for holding the congregation despite a ban on public gatherings being issued by the [[Government of Delhi]] on 13 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat draws widespread condemnation from Muslim society |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/academics-among-muslims-condemn-the-act-of-tablighi-jamaat-in-nizamuddin/article31218658.ece |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Hindu Business Line}}</ref> According to the Home Ministry, there were 1,746 people in the Markaz on 21 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat's defiance spreads concern {{!}} India Today Insight |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/web-exclusive/story/the-new-threat-from-tablighi-jamaat-1661938-2020-04-01 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref>\n\n==Attendees==\n\nAt least 9000 attendees from all over the country and from abroad participated in the congregation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/americans-british-among-960-foreign-tablighi-jamaat-members-blacklisted-visas-cancelled-2563029.html|title=Americans, British Among 960 Foreign Tablighi Jamaat Members Blacklisted, Visas Cancelled|website=News18|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/1400-nizamuddin-event-attendees-from-maha-traced-tope/articleshow/74965665.cms|title=1,400 Nizamuddin event attendees from Maha traced: Tope|date=2020-04-03|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Over 800 Indonesian and Malaysian preachers present. Many of these attendees are untraceable and are absconding.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qz.com/india/1828919/delhis-tablighi-jamaat-event-becomes-indias-coronavirus-hotspot/|title=A religious congregation in Delhi could be the coronavirus hotspot India was trying to escape|first=Niharika|last=Sharma|website=Quartz India}}</ref> 281 foreigners among 1830 people who had been staying at the mosque since 8 March were found by Delhi Police.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nAbout 200 people have shown symptoms of COVID-19 of which, 53 people have been confirmed positive in Delhi.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-52104753|title=India event sparks massive search for Covid-19 cases|date=2020-03-31|work=BBC News|access-date=2020-03-31|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/opinion/tablighi-jamaat-congregation-and-how-religion-has-been-the-super-spreader-of-coronavirus/392531/|title=Tablighi Jamaat congregation and how religion has been the 'super spreader' of coronavirus|last=Team|first=ThePrint|date=2020-04-01|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gulte.com/news/83733/More-Than-330-Cases-Linked-to-Delhi-Mosque|title=More Than 330 Cases Linked to Delhi Mosque|last=13|date=2020-04-02|website=Gulte|language=english|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref> The state of [[Tamil Nadu]] reported more than 190 cases linked to the event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-india-delhi-markaz-nizamuddin-mosque-sealed-after-7-covid-19-deaths-850-moved-out-for-qu-2203336|title=50 Coronavirus Cases In Tamil Nadu After Delhi Mosque Event: 10 Points|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-31}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath==\nThere was Ijtema (congregation) in every week of March till March 21.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/2100-foreigners-visited-india-for-tablighi-activities-this-year-mha/articleshow/74915572.cms|title=2100 foreigners visited India for Tablighi activities this year: MHA|date=March 31, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/nizamuddin-corona-cases-govts-race-to-curb-spread-as-hundreds-from-tablighi-meet-show-coronavirus-symptoms/articleshow/74921860.cms|title=Nizamuddin corona cases: Govts race to curb spread as hundreds from Tablighi meet show symptoms &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref> There were also other violation of rules by foreign speakers including misuse of tourist visa for missionary activities and not taking 14-day home quarantine for travellers from abroad.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Singh|first=Vijaita|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/home-ministry-to-blacklist-800-tablighi-preachers-from-indonesia-for-violation-of-visa-rules/article31214048.ece|title=Home Ministry asked States to identify 824 foreign Tablighi members|date=2020-03-31|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> It is believed that the sources of infection were preachers from Indonesia. At least 24 of the attendees had tested positive for the virus among 300 who showed symptom by 31 March 2020.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-52104753 |title=Coronavirus: Search for hundreds of people after Delhi prayer meeting |date=31 March 2020 |work=BBC }}</ref> Many had returned to their states and also provided refuge to foreign speakers without the knowledge of local governments.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Saravanan|first=S. p|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/covid-19-five-tourists-from-thailand-admitted-to-isolation-ward-at-erode-hospital/article31088949.ece|title=COVID-19 {{!}} Five tourists from Thailand admitted to isolation ward at Erode hospital|date=2020-03-17|work=The Hindu|access-date=2020-04-02|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref> and eventually started local transmissions especially in [[Tamil Nadu]], [[Telengana]], [[Karnataka]], [[Jammu and Kashmir]] and [[Assam]]. On 16 March 2020, Delhi Government ordered that no religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 will be allowed in Delhi till 31 March 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/covid-19-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-protests-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-mar-31/articleshow/74650645.cms|title=Coronavirus in Delhi: No religious, social, political gatherings, protests of over 50 in Delhi till Mar 31 &#124; India News - Times of India|website=The Times of India}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/coronavirus-outbreak-no-religious-social-political-gatherings-of-over-50-in-delhi-till-march-31/articleshow/74650421.cms?from=mdr|title=Coronavirus outbreak: No religious, social, political gatherings of over 50 in Delhi till March 31|date=March 16, 2020|via=The Economic Times}}</ref> As of 30 March 2020 the entire [[Nizamuddin West]] area has been cordoned off by the Police and medical camps have been set up.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/coronavirus-200-people-from-nizamuddin-develop-symptoms-area-cordoned-off/article31204617.ece|title=Coronavirus &#124; 200 people in Nizamuddin develop symptoms; area cordoned off|first=Saurabh|last=Trivedi|date=March 30, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref> After evacuation from the markaz, of the scores of jamaat attendees, 167 of them were quarantined in a railway facility in south east Delhi amid concerns over their safety and transmission of the virus. There were further complications after the staff at the quarantine facility reported the Tablighi jamaat followers misbehaved with the staff and spit at the doctors looking after them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-india-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-misbehave-staffers-spit-doctors-delhi-quarantine-units-1662322-2020-04-01|title=Tablighi Jamaat attendees misbehave with staffers, spit at doctors at Delhi quarantine units|last=DelhiApril 1|first=Press Trust of India New|last2=April 1|first2=2020UPDATED:|website=India Today|language=en|access-date=2020-04-02|last3=Ist|first3=2020 22:59}}</ref>\n\nAdministration of TJ had said they are willing to dispatch hundreds of missionary to their respective nation & states but as the lockdown is in place they are helpless.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/nizamuddin-markaz-had-sought-help-from-authorities-for-vacating-premises/article31214305.ece|title=Nizamuddin markaz had sought help from authorities for vacating premises|first=Staff|last=Reporter|date=March 31, 2020|via=www.thehindu.com}}</ref><ref>Press Release and relevant letters released by the Markaz</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://khabar.ndtv.com/news/india/coronavirus-total-case-in-india-nizamuddin-markaz-organiser-says-continuously-asking-curfew-pass-and-2203440|title=\u0915\u094c\u0928 \u0939\u0948 '\u0918\u094b\u0930 \u0905\u092a\u0930\u093e\u0927\u0940': \u0905\u0917\u0930 \u0924\u092c\u0932\u0940\u0917\u0940 \u091c\u092e\u093e\u0924 \u0928\u0947 \u092e\u093e\u0902\u0917\u093e \u0925\u093e 17 \u0917\u093e\u0921\u093c\u093f\u092f\u094b\u0902 \u0915\u093e \u0915\u0930\u094d\u092b\u094d\u092f\u0942 \u092a\u093e\u0938, \u0924\u094b \u0915\u093f\u0938\u0928\u0947 \u0928\u0939\u0940\u0902 \u0938\u0941\u0928\u0940 \u092c\u093e\u0924|website=NDTVIndia}}</ref>\n\n==Cases linked==\n\nAccording health authorities, until 2. April, among 2000 positive cases in India nearly 400 cases epidemiological linkage can be traced to the Tablighi Jamaat cluster.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theprint.in/india/one-in-indias-five-covid-19-patients-is-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-and-its-delhi-event/393993/|title=One in India\u2019s five Covid-19 patients is linked to Tablighi Jamaat and its Delhi event|last=Yadavar|first=Swagata|date=2020-04-02|website=ThePrint|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/400-covid-19-cases-with-linkage-to-tablighi-jamaat-found-health-ministry/articleshow/74951562.cms|title=400 COVID-19 cases with linkage to Tablighi Jamaat found: Health Ministry {{!}} India News - Times of India|last=Apr 2|first=ANI {{!}}|last2=2020|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03|last3=Ist|first3=18:55}}</ref> Following are some of the  positive cases from different states as reported in media with traces to this cluster.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! State !! Positive Cases \n!Deaths!! Ref(s)\n|-\n|[[Andhra Pradesh|