{"title_page": "Kampong Speu Province", "text_new": "{{Short description|Province of Cambodia}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Kampong Speu Province\n| native_name             = {{nobold|{{lang|km|\u1781\u17c1\u178f\u17d2\u178f\u1780\u17c6\u1796\u1784\u17cb\u179f\u17d2\u1796\u17ba}}}}\n| native_name_lang        = km<!-- ISO 639-2 code -->\n| settlement_type         = [[Provinces of Cambodia|Province]]\n| image_skyline           = Kampong Speu.jpg\n| image_caption           = A flooded field in Kampong Speu\n| image_flag              = \n| image_seal              = Kampong Speu seal.png\n| image_shield            = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = Cambodia Kampong Speu locator map.svg\n| map_caption             = Map of Cambodia highlighting Kampong Speu\n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location of Kampong Speu in Cambodia\n| coordinates             = {{coord|11|30|N|104|20|E|type:adm1st_region:KH|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{CAM}}\n| established_title       = Provincial status\n| established_date        = 1907 \n| seat_type               = Capital<!-- Capital -->\n| seat                    = [[Chbar Mon Municipality]] \n| leader_party            = [[Cambodian People's Party|CPP]]\n| leader_title            = Governor\n| leader_name             = Vei Samnang \n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_total_km2          = 7017 \n| area_rank               = 11th\n| area_note               = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| population_footnotes    = <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/open?id=1cT5HDmeYn3SDZySlfvFMi6q-EhzyqBbu/|title=General Population Census of the Kingdom of Cambodia 2019|publisher=[[Ministry of Planning (Cambodia)|Ministry of Planning]]|work=National Institute of Statistics|date=June 2019|accessdate=12 August 2019}}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>  \n| population_total        = {{increase}} 872219\n| population_rank         = 8th\n| population_density_rank = 11th  \n| population_as_of        = 2019 census\n| population_density_km2  = 124  \n| population_demonym      = \n| population_note         = \n| blank_name_sec1         = [[Districts of Cambodia|Districts]]\n| blank_info_sec1         = 8\n| blank1_name_sec1        = <!-- Communes -->\n| blank1_info_sec1        = \n| blank2_name_sec1        = <!-- Villages -->\n| blank2_info_sec1        = \n| timezone1               = [[UTC+7]] (ICT)\n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          = Dialing code\n| area_code               = +855\n| iso_code                = KH-5\n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n{{Contains Khmer text}}\n'''Kampong Speu''' ({{lang-km|\u1781\u17c1\u178f\u17d2\u178f\u1780\u17c6\u1796\u1784\u17cb\u179f\u17d2\u1796\u17ba}}, {{IPA-km|k\u0251mp\u0254\u02d0\u014b sp\u0268\u02d0|IPA}}, <small>\"[[Carambola|Starfruit]] Port\"</small>) is a [[provinces of Cambodia|province]] (''khaet'') of [[Cambodia]]. It borders the provinces of [[Pursat]] and [[Kompong Chhnang Province|Kompong Chhnang]] to the north, [[Kandal Province|Kandal]] to the east, [[Tak\u00e9o Province|Tak\u00e9o]] to the southeast, [[Kampot Province|Kampot]] to the south and [[Koh Kong Province|Koh Kong]] to the west. Its capital is [[Chbar Mon]] town.\n\n==Etymology==\n''Kampong Speu'' in [[Khmer language|Khmer]] means \"starfruit port\" or \"starfruit harbor\". In Khmer, ''kampong'' is a place-name element, meaning \"port\" or \"harbor\". It derives from the [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]], [[Malay language|Malay]], in which it means \"village\". ''Speu'' in the Khmer language means \"starfruit\".\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nThe province is subdivided into 7 districts and 1 municipality.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! ISO Code\n! District\n! Khmer\n|-\n| 05-01\n| [[Basedth District|Basedth]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1794\u179a\u179f\u17c1\u178a\u17d2\u178b}}\n|-\n| 05-02\n| [[Chbar Mon Municipality]]\n| {{lang|km|\u1780\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1784\u1785\u17d2\u1794\u17b6\u179a\u1798\u1793}}\n|-\n| 05-03\n| [[Kong Pisei District|Kong Pisei]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1782\u1784\u1796\u17b7\u179f\u17b8}}\n|-\n| 05-04\n| [[Aoral District|Aoral]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u17b1\u179a\u17c9\u17b6\u179b\u17cb}}\n|-\n| 05-05\n| [[Oudong District|Oudong]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u17a7\u178a\u17bb\u1784\u17d2\u1782}}\n|-\n| 05-06\n| [[Phnom Sruoch District|Phnom Sruoch]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1797\u17d2\u1793\u17c6\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bd\u1785}}\n|-\n| 05-07\n| [[Samraong Tong District|Samraong Tong]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u179f\u17c6\u179a\u17c4\u1784\u1791\u1784}}\n|-\n| 05-08\n| [[Thpong District|Thpong]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1790\u17d2\u1796\u1784}}\n|}\n\n== Economy ==\nThe Wing Star Shoes factory in Kampong Speu Province manufactures [[ASICS|Asics]] sports shoes. It collapsed in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2013-05-18/cambodia-factory-collapse-how-did-inspectors-miss-it|title=Cambodia factory collapse: How did inspectors miss it?|last=Chen|first=Dene-Hern|date=May 18, 2013|website=Public Radio International|language=en|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref> Three people were killed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cambodia-collapse-idUSBRE94F04S20130516|title=Roof collapse at Cambodian shoe plant kills three - minister|date=2013-05-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-02-18|language=en}}</ref> Workers struck at the Wing Star Shoes Factory in 2014, blocking National Route 3, and demanding a $5 raise in bonuses and enforcement of labor laws.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cambodiadaily.com/news/as-wing-star-shoes-strike-enters-third-day-workers-block-road-54559/|title=As Wing Star Shoes Strike Enters Third Day, Workers Block Road|last=Pheap|first=Aun|date=2014-03-20|website=The Cambodia Daily|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref> In 2016 and 2018, mass faintings of workers were reported. The cause in 2016, initially attributed to a worker having been possessed by a \"spirit,\" was later revised to \"poor health and imagination.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phnompenhapost.com/national/spirit-initially-blamed-shoe-factory-fainting|title=\u2018Spirit\u2019 initially blamed for shoe factory fainting|last=Kong Meta|date=November 3, 2016|website=[[Phnom Penh Post]]}}</ref> 2018, police reported that after a worker had a seizure, her \"scream caused a mass panic, prompting workers to run, feel dizzy and faint.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khmertimeskh.com/50542730/dozens-of-workers-faint-at-shoe-factory-2/|title=Dozens of workers faint at shoe factory|last=Mom Kunthear|date=2018-10-21|website=Khmer Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref>\n== Attraction ==\n=== Phnom Aural ===\n[[File:Phom Aoral.jpg|thumb|right|Phnom Aural Peak is the second peak from the left in the mountains behind]]\n[[Phnom Aural]] is the tallest peak in Cambodia. It is 1,813 meters tall (other sources give elevations between 1,771 and 1,667 meters). It is in the eastern part of the Cardamom Mountains. To protect the biodiversity of the mountains, [[Phnom Aural Wildlife Sanctuary]] was established.\nThis mountain in located in Aoral District, Kampong Speu Province.\n\n===Oudong===\nLocated at the foothill of the mountain Phnom [[Oudong]], about 40 km northwest of the modern capital Phnom Penh, Oudong was royal residence and Cambodia's capital for more than 250 years until 1866. A monumental royal necropolis of sovereigns of several centuries is scattered on top the prominent bisected mountain, which runs from the southeast to the northeast.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.phnompenhpost.com/national/buddha-chinese-deception   |title= The Buddha of Chinese deception Oudong Mountain by Bou Saroeun |publisher=  Phnom Penh Post |date= 22 June 2001  |accessdate=26 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web   |url=http://www.khmerstudies.org/download-files/events/conferences/Phnom%20Bakheng%20Workshop/Claude%20Jacques%20-%2023-40.pdf?lbisphpreq=1   |title=THistory of the Phnom Bakheng Monument   |publisher=Khmer Studies   |date=   |accessdate=26 June 2015   |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626103427/http://www.khmerstudies.org/download-files/events/conferences/Phnom%20Bakheng%20Workshop/Claude%20Jacques%20-%2023-40.pdf?lbisphpreq=1   |archive-date=26 June 2015   |url-status=dead   }}</ref>\n<div class=\"left\">\n{|\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n[[File:Udong 0001.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Phnom Oudong]]\n|}\n</div>\n\n===Kirirom National Park===\n<div class=\"left\">\n{|\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n[[File:2 Chambak waterwall 21-11-2010 - panoramio.jpg|thumb|200px|Chambok waterfall]]\n|valign=\"top\"|\n[[File:Kirirom National Park.jpg|thumb|200x|A natural lake in Kirirom]]\n|}\n</div>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.world-wildlife-adventures.com/directory/cambodia/wildlife-park.asp?sanctuary=Kirirom+National+Park&state=Kompong+Speu+and+Koh+Kong+Provinces Kirirom National Park, Cambodia]\n\n{{Geographic location\n|Centre    = Kompong Speu Province\n|North     = [[Kompong Chhnang Province]]\n|Northeast = \n|East      = [[Kandal Province]]\n|Southeast = [[Tak\u00e9o Province]]\n|South     = [[Kampot Province]]\n|Southwest = \n|West      = [[Koh Kong Province]]\n|Northwest = [[Pursat Province]]\n}}\n\n{{Provinces of Cambodia}}\n{{Portal bar|Cambodia}}\n\n[[Category:Kampong Speu Province| ]]\n[[Category:Provinces of Cambodia]]\n\n\n{{cambodia-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Province of Cambodia}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                    = Kampong Speu Province\n| native_name             = {{nobold|{{lang|km|\u1781\u17c1\u178f\u17d2\u178f\u1780\u17c6\u1796\u1784\u17cb\u179f\u17d2\u1796\u17ba}}}}\n| native_name_lang        = km<!-- ISO 639-2 code -->\n| settlement_type         = [[Provinces of Cambodia|Province]]\n| image_skyline           = Kampong Speu.jpg\n| image_caption           = A flooded field in Kampong Speu\n| image_flag              = \n| image_seal              = Kampong Speu seal.png\n| image_shield            = \n| nickname                = \n| motto                   = \n| image_map               = Cambodia Kampong Speu locator map.svg\n| map_caption             = Map of Cambodia highlighting Kampong Speu\n| pushpin_map             = \n| pushpin_label_position  = \n| pushpin_map_caption     = Location of Kampong Speu in Cambodia\n| coordinates             = {{coord|11|30|N|104|20|E|type:adm1st_region:KH|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_footnotes   = \n| subdivision_type        = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name        = {{CAM}}\n| established_title       = Provincial status\n| established_date        = 1907 \n| seat_type               = Capital<!-- Capital -->\n| seat                    = [[Chbar Mon Municipality]] \n| leader_party            = [[Cambodian People's Party|CPP]]\n| leader_title            = Governor\n| leader_name             = Vei Samnang \n| area_footnotes          = \n| area_total_km2          = 7017 \n| area_rank               = 11th\n| area_note               = \n| elevation_footnotes     = \n| elevation_m             = \n| population_footnotes    = <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://drive.google.com/open?id=1cT5HDmeYn3SDZySlfvFMi6q-EhzyqBbu/|title=General Population Census of the Kingdom of Cambodia 2019|publisher=[[Ministry of Planning (Cambodia)|Ministry of Planning]]|work=National Institute of Statistics|date=June 2019|accessdate=12 August 2019}}{{Dead link|date=February 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>  \n| population_total        = {{increase}} 872219\n| population_rank         = 8th\n| population_density_rank = 11th  \n| population_as_of        = 2019 census\n| population_density_km2  = 124  \n| population_demonym      = \n| population_note         = \n| blank_name_sec1         = [[Districts of Cambodia|Districts]]\n| blank_info_sec1         = 8\n| blank1_name_sec1        = <!-- Communes -->\n| blank1_info_sec1        = \n| blank2_name_sec1        = <!-- Villages -->\n| blank2_info_sec1        = \n| timezone1               = [[UTC+7]] (ICT)\n| postal_code_type        = \n| postal_code             = \n| area_code_type          = Dialing code\n| area_code               = +855\n| iso_code                = KH-5\n| website                 = \n| footnotes               = \n}}\n{{Contains Khmer text}}\n'''Kampong Speu''' ({{lang-km|\u1781\u17c1\u178f\u17d2\u178f\u1780\u17c6\u1796\u1784\u17cb\u179f\u17d2\u1796\u17ba}}, {{IPA-km|k\u0251mp\u0254\u02d0\u014b sp\u0268\u02d0|IPA}}, <small>\"[[Carambola|Starfruit]] Port\"</small>) is a [[provinces of Cambodia|province]] (''khaet'') of [[Cambodia]]. It borders the provinces of [[Pursat]] and [[Kompong Chhnang Province|Kompong Chhnang]] to the north, [[Kandal Province|Kandal]] to the east, [[Tak\u00e9o Province|Tak\u00e9o]] to the southeast, [[Kampot Province|Kampot]] to the south and [[Koh Kong Province|Koh Kong]] to the west. Its capital is [[Chbar Mon]] town.\n\n==Etymology==\n''Kampong Speu'' in [[Khmer language|Khmer]] means \"starfruit port\" or \"starfruit harbor\". In Khmer, ''kampong'' is a place-name element, meaning \"port\" or \"harbor\". It derives from the [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian language]], [[Malay language|Malay]], in which it means \"village\". ''Speu'' in the Khmer language means \"starfruit\".\n\n==Administrative divisions==\nThe province is subdivided into 7 districts and 1 municipality.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! ISO Code\n! District\n! Khmer\n|-\n| 05-01\n| [[Basedth District|Basedth]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1794\u179a\u179f\u17c1\u178a\u17d2\u178b}}\n|-\n| 05-02\n| [[Chbar Mon Municipality]]\n| {{lang|km|\u1780\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1784\u1785\u17d2\u1794\u17b6\u179a\u1798\u1793}}\n|-\n| 05-03\n| [[Kong Pisei District|Kong Pisei]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1782\u1784\u1796\u17b7\u179f\u17b8}}\n|-\n| 05-04\n| [[Aoral District|Aoral]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u17b1\u179a\u17c9\u17b6\u179b\u17cb}}\n|-\n| 05-05\n| [[Oudong District|Oudong]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u17a7\u178a\u17bb\u1784\u17d2\u1782}}\n|-\n| 05-06\n| [[Phnom Sruoch District|Phnom Sruoch]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1797\u17d2\u1793\u17c6\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bd\u1785}}\n|-\n| 05-07\n| [[Samraong Tong District|Samraong Tong]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u179f\u17c6\u179a\u17c4\u1784\u1791\u1784}}\n|-\n| 05-08\n| [[Thpong District|Thpong]]\n| {{lang|km|\u179f\u17d2\u179a\u17bb\u1780\u1790\u17d2\u1796\u1784}}\n|}\n\n== Economy ==\nThe Wing Star Shoes factory in Kampong Speu Province manufactures [[ASICS|Asics]] sports shoes. It collapsed in 2013.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pri.org/stories/2013-05-18/cambodia-factory-collapse-how-did-inspectors-miss-it|title=Cambodia factory collapse: How did inspectors miss it?|last=Chen|first=Dene-Hern|date=May 18, 2013|website=Public Radio International|language=en|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref> Three people were killed.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-cambodia-collapse-idUSBRE94F04S20130516|title=Roof collapse at Cambodian shoe plant kills three - minister|date=2013-05-16|work=Reuters|access-date=2019-02-18|language=en}}</ref> Workers struck at the Wing Star Shoes Factory in 2014, blocking National Route 3, and demanding a $5 raise in bonuses and enforcement of labor laws.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cambodiadaily.com/news/as-wing-star-shoes-strike-enters-third-day-workers-block-road-54559/|title=As Wing Star Shoes Strike Enters Third Day, Workers Block Road|last=Pheap|first=Aun|date=2014-03-20|website=The Cambodia Daily|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref> In 2016 and 2018, mass faintings of workers were reported. The cause in 2016, initially attributed to a worker having been possessed by a \"spirit,\" was later revised to \"poor health and imagination.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.phnompenhapost.com/national/spirit-initially-blamed-shoe-factory-fainting|title=\u2018Spirit\u2019 initially blamed for shoe factory fainting|last=Kong Meta|date=November 3, 2016|website=[[Phnom Penh Post]]}}</ref> 2018, police reported that after a worker had a seizure, her \"scream caused a mass panic, prompting workers to run, feel dizzy and faint.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.khmertimeskh.com/50542730/dozens-of-workers-faint-at-shoe-factory-2/|title=Dozens of workers faint at shoe factory|last=Mom Kunthear|date=2018-10-21|website=Khmer Times|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-18}}</ref>\n== Attraction ==\n=== Phnom Aural ===\n[[File:Phom Aoral.jpg|thumb|right|Phnom Aural Peak is the second peak from the left in the mountains behind]]\n[[Phnom Aural]] is the tallest peak in Cambodia. It is 1,813 meters tall (other sources give elevations between 1,771 and 1,667 meters). It is in the eastern part of the Cardamom Mountains. To protect the biodiversity of the mountains, Phnom Aural Wildlife Sanctuary was established.\nThis mountain in located in Aoral District, Kampong Speu Province.\n\n===Oudong===\nLocated at the foothill of the mountain Phnom [[Oudong]], about 40 km northwest of the modern capital Phnom Penh, Oudong was royal residence and Cambodia's capital for more than 250 years until 1866. A monumental royal necropolis of sovereigns of several centuries is scattered on top the prominent bisected mountain, which runs from the southeast to the northeast.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.phnompenhpost.com/national/buddha-chinese-deception   |title= The Buddha of Chinese deception Oudong Mountain by Bou Saroeun |publisher=  Phnom Penh Post |date= 22 June 2001  |accessdate=26 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web   |url=http://www.khmerstudies.org/download-files/events/conferences/Phnom%20Bakheng%20Workshop/Claude%20Jacques%20-%2023-40.pdf?lbisphpreq=1   |title=THistory of the Phnom Bakheng Monument   |publisher=Khmer Studies   |date=   |accessdate=26 June 2015   |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626103427/http://www.khmerstudies.org/download-files/events/conferences/Phnom%20Bakheng%20Workshop/Claude%20Jacques%20-%2023-40.pdf?lbisphpreq=1   |archive-date=26 June 2015   |url-status=dead   }}</ref>\n<div class=\"left\">\n{|\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n[[File:Udong 0001.jpg|thumb|250px|right|Phnom Oudong]]\n|}\n</div>\n\n===Kirirom National Park===\n<div class=\"left\">\n{|\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n[[File:2 Chambak waterwall 21-11-2010 - panoramio.jpg|thumb|200px|Chambok waterfall]]\n|valign=\"top\"|\n[[File:Kirirom National Park.jpg|thumb|200x|A natural lake in Kirirom]]\n|}\n</div>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.world-wildlife-adventures.com/directory/cambodia/wildlife-park.asp?sanctuary=Kirirom+National+Park&state=Kompong+Speu+and+Koh+Kong+Provinces Kirirom National Park, Cambodia]\n\n{{Geographic location\n|Centre    = Kompong Speu Province\n|North     = [[Kompong Chhnang Province]]\n|Northeast = \n|East      = [[Kandal Province]]\n|Southeast = [[Tak\u00e9o Province]]\n|South     = [[Kampot Province]]\n|Southwest = \n|West      = [[Koh Kong Province]]\n|Northwest = [[Pursat Province]]\n}}\n\n{{Provinces of Cambodia}}\n{{Portal bar|Cambodia}}\n\n[[Category:Kampong Speu Province| ]]\n[[Category:Provinces of Cambodia]]\n\n\n{{cambodia-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Tbennert", "label": "safe", "comment": "wikilink", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kampong_Speu_Province"}
